dbl:section:
Miscellaneous When you pass an 8bit string in the constructor of an &xist; element, or sgmlop passes a string to &xist;, these strings have to be converted to Unicode. &xist; assumes that these 8bit strings are in the system default encoding, which is &ascii;. If you want to change this you can put a script named sitecustomize.py somewhere in the Python path, with the following content:
import sys sys.setdefaultencoding("iso-8859-1")
(or any other encoding name, that you want to use instead of "iso-8859-1").
